    <!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutrals & Soft Blue -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-page, vertical scrolling application designed as a "sugoroku" (Japanese board game) path. The structure is chronological, divided into four thematic chapters to provide narrative structure to the 22-year journey. Key interactions include scrolling to follow the path, and clicking to open a modal with details. This structure was chosen because it directly mimics the "sugoroku" concept, turning a linear life story into an engaging, game-like exploratory experience that is intuitive and memorable. The goal is integrated as the final step in the chronological journey. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        1. Life Path (HTML/CSS): Report Info -> Chronological life events. Goal -> Organize/Show Change. Viz -> A visual, winding path made with Tailwind CSS. Interaction -> User scrolls to navigate. Justification -> Creates an immersive journey, guiding the user through the story.
        2. Milestone Cards (HTML/CSS): Report Info -> Each year's event. Goal -> Inform. Viz -> Interactive cards along the path. Interaction -> Click to open a modal with the event description. Justification -> Breaks down the story into digestible pieces and encourages engagement.
        3. Goal Section (HTML/CSS): Report Info -> Future aspirations. Goal -> Inform/Inspire. Viz -> A prominent, final milestone. Interaction -> Part of the natural scroll flow. Justification -> Provides a clear conclusion to the life story and connects directly to the 22-year journey.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Noto Sans JP', sans-serif;
            background-color: #FDFCF8;
